@startuml

' Define classes and their relationships

class Sensor {
    +String vendorId
    +String description
    +String unit
    +Room room
    +getMeasurements(): List<Measurement>
    +getLastValue(): Measurement
}

abstract class AbstractSensor {
    +String vendorId
    +String description
    +String unit
    +Room room
    +getMeasurements(): List<Measurement>
    +getLastValue(): Measurement
}

class TemperatureSensor extends AbstractSensor {
    +float minValue
    +float maxValue
}

class PowerSensor extends AbstractSensor {
    +float totalConsumption
}

class Measurement {
    +Timestamp timestamp
    +float value
}

class Room {
    +String description
    +List<Sensor> sensors
}

class Apartment {
    +Address address
    +List<Room> rooms
    +List<Inhabitant> inhabitants
    +String email
}

class Inhabitant {
    +String username
    +String password
    +boolean isAdmin
    +getSensors(): List<Sensor>
    +setThreshold(Sensor, float): void
}

class SensorController {
    +registerSensor(Sensor): void
    +login(username: String, password: String): boolean
    +getApartmentInfo(): Apartment
    +storeMeasurement(sensor: Sensor, measurement: Measurement): void
}

class EMonitor {
    +checkThresholds(): void
    +sendAlert(email: String, message: String): void
}

class Address {
    +String street
    +int houseNumber
    +String city
    +String postalCode
}

' Relationships

Apartment "1" *-- "many" Room : contains
Room "1" *-- "many" Sensor : contains
Apartment "1" *-- "many" Inhabitant : has
SensorController "1" -- "1" Apartment : manages
SensorController "1" -- "many" Sensor : monitors
EMonitor "1" -- "1" SensorController : interacts with
Inhabitant "1" -- "many" Sensor : can configure
Inhabitant "1" -- "1" Apartment : belongs to
Sensor "1" -- "1" Room : assigned to

@enduml

---

### 🔍 Explanation of Key Elements:

- **Sensor**: Base class for all sensor types.
- **AbstractSensor**: Used to avoid duplication in behavior between `TemperatureSensor` and `PowerSensor`.
- **TemperatureSensor / PowerSensor**: Specific implementations with unique properties.
- **Measurement**: Stores a timestamped reading from a sensor.
- **Room**: Contains sensors and has a descriptive name.
- **Apartment**: Has an address and multiple rooms; may have alert emails.
- **Inhabitant**: User of the system with login credentials and possibly admin rights.
- **SensorController**: Central system for managing sensors, users, and data.
- **EMonitor**: External system that checks thresholds and sends alerts.
- **Address**: Simple class to store apartment location details.

